mothering up
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:a matching or reunion of natural ewe and lamb in a large mob of sheep and lambs [especially after a muster, docking.]


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See: re-mothering
